    <p>This hy­brid doc­u­men­tary film ex­plores the con­flict faced by trauma ther­a­pist Poh Lin Lee, who works in the Aus­tralian De­ten­tion Cen­tre for Asy­lum Seek­ers on Christ­mas Is­land. Mean­while, the yearly crab mi­gra­tion takes place and lo­cals per­form rit­u­als for ghosts. The screen­ing is part of the Asian Film Ar­chive’s Re­frame: The (In) Hos­pitable World pro­gramme, which fea­tures thought-pro­vok­ing films from var­i­ous coun­tries that ex­plore cur­rent eco­log­i­cal and en­vi­ron­men­tal crises.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Old­ham The­atre,</p>
    <p>One Can­ning Rise MRT: City Hall/</p>
    <p>Bras Basah WHEN: To­mor­row, 8pm AD­MIS­SION: $10 INFO: bit.ly/2GNuTGU</p>


